                        The Daily Record (Baltimore, MD)

                             August 2, 2016 Tuesday

U.S. News: Johns Hopkins 4th in nation for hospitals

BYLINE: Daniel Leaderman

SECTION: NEWS

LENGTH: 197  words


The Johns Hopkins Hospital has once again earned high marks in U.S. News & World
Report's annual hospital rankings, but moved from third in the nation to fourth
on this year's honor roll.

The top five hospitals for 2016-2017 are the Mayo Clinic in Minnesota, the
Cleveland Clinic, Massachusetts General Hospital in Boston, Hopkins, and UCLA
Medical Center in Los Angeles.

Hopkins once dominated the list, nabbing the top spot in 22 out of the first 24
years the ranking were published.

The hospital earned particularly high marks for its departments of rheumatology
and neurology and neurosurgery.

Hopkins also took the top spot among Maryland hospitals; rounding out the
statewide top ten are:

2. University of Maryland Medical Center;

3. Mercy Medical Center; Sinai Hospital of Baltimore (tie);

5.  MedStar Southern Maryland Hospital Center;

6.  MedStar Union Memorial Hospital Center; University of Maryland St. Joseph
Hospital Center (tie);

8.  Anne Arundel Medical Center; MedStar Franklin Square Medical Center (tie);

10. MedStar Harbor Hospital.











